title: Welcome
author: Ogel6000
pages:
#- The Saraliana Protectorate is officially neutral, though we will defend our buffer land and secrecy to the greatest of our potential. This is why we settled in this location.
#- The land you settled in is not officially claimed by the Saraliana Protectorate, but is used by us as closely guarded buffer lands: a zone in between us and others which we would prefer to remain neutral territory.
#- Because it is officially not claimed by us, your encroachment into this land is not so much a direct violation of our law nor does it demand further actions in any way.
#- You are also within 50 blocks of a fortress known as Arx, an active province of Fellowship, whom I have been informed you settled close to earlier. We are close allies to Arx, and will defend them as our own.
#- I strongly recommend you rethink your location. Deep knowledge about a location is pretty important to thrive in Civcraft, and it seems you have settled multiple times without knowledge about your location.
#- Our offer of buying your location OR paying you the full value of your project is an offer which still be available permanently. If you choose not, that is fine.
#- Additionally, should you desire to stay in this location, we would like to offer your town admittance into the Saraliana Protectorate.

Should you accept, you will immediately be treated as an allie, though must acknowledge yourself
#- as a province of us. Should you choose admittance as a province, we will respect your liberty, and not infringe on your rights in any way.
#- I apologise for coming on hard, but we don't take lightly to encroachment. Please inform me as to your actions as soon as your town has reached a decision.

#- 